Jacob L. Lew has been confirmed as the Director of the Office of Management and Budget with bipartisan support. President Obama is pleased with Lew's appointment, stating that he brings extensive experience and wisdom to the role at a critical time in the nation's history. The President emphasizes the need for tough choices to restore fiscal stability, promote job creation, and economic growth. He expresses confidence in Lew's ability to lead these efforts and looks forward to working with him.